// TEST: effect_unhandled_no_handler_in_scope
// EXPECT: error E1001 at 25:8
// §10.3: a function that invokes an effect operation with NO Layer-1 (`handling`
// block) and NO Layer-2 (`handle ... with`) handler in scope, and which does not
// declare the effect in its own `with` clause, is a compile-time error. Here
// `main` invokes the `Log` effect operation `log` with no handler installed and
// no `with Log` clause.
//
// Observed diagnostic: a genuinely-unhandled bare op surfaces as the resolver's
// undefined-name error E1001 (at the `log(...)` call site, 25:8), NOT the
// capability pass's E8020. Effect ops are injected into scope ONLY in
// handler-in-scope contexts — a `with` clause, an effect impl method, a
// `handling` block, or a module with a matching `handle` — so with none of
// those present, `log` is simply an undefined name. E8020 fires only on
// `EffectOp` AIR nodes, which are never constructed from a surface bare-op
// `Call`; unifying the two (so an unhandled op reports E8020) is a separate
// follow-up (Q-effect-op-node-lowering) and is intentionally out of scope here.
module effects_unhandled_effect_error

effect Log {
  fn log(message: String) -> Void
}

fn main() {
  log("no handler is installed for Log")
}
